      "raw_text": "The Northern Pacific Is found to\nhave increased it's SIDE tracks during\nthe year by 1908 feet. the Great\nNorthern by 34.s5s feet. the o. r.. a\nN. by 1895 feet and the Union Depot\ncompany by 1879 feet. There is an\nactual decrease in the case OF the\ns. f. 4 N. owing to the, removal of\nstation and bS6s feet of side tracks.\n\n\nIn the way of furniture and ma\nchinery the Northern Pacific has in\ncreased In value about $4,000 and\nin buildings about 5000: the Great\nNorthern, machinery in Hillyard\nshops, $751; and IN buildings. $10.-\nss5.\n\n\nThe item Of Pullman coaches used\nby the o. r. & N. and not included\nIn Its figures. does not appear In last\nyears roll. nor for several years back."
